{
  "answer": "**Manusmṛti chapter 3 does not mention *madhuparka* (the honey-mixture offered in hospitality) or specify rules about which guests deserve it.**[^1]\n\nThis chapter focuses on the transition from studentship to the householder stage, marriage rules (including forms of marriage, suitable brides, and progeny), and duties toward women.[^1] The *madhuparka* hospitality rules appear instead in chapter 4 (e.g., for a *guru*, father-in-law, or maternal uncle returning after a year, or certain Brahmanas at sacrifices).[^2][^3]\n\n[^1]: *Manusmṛti*, [Chapter 3](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/03/translation/).\n\n[^2]: *Manusmṛti*, Chapter 4, [p-c1f760](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/04/translation/#p-c1f760).\n\n[^3]: *Manusmṛti*, Chapter 4, [p-0c0be7](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/04/translation/#p-0c0be7).",
